    "summary": "Solving complex problems is what energises me. Working together on solutions that matter, and do not end up in a bottom drawer, while also having fun in the process. I have a strong drive and set the bar high. I enjoy investing time in my team, have a passion for coaching and educating others and facilitating their growth. I am able to present a compelling view and connect with different stakeholders, by truly listening to others and being genuinely interested in people.\n\nI am a Finance and M&A professional with excellent analytical & reporting skills, extensive experience in managing complex, high-pressure due diligence processes and a strong track record in coaching and developing junior staff.\n\nCurrently I am a Director Deals (M&A) at the Financial due diligence department of PwC, with a specific focus on Health Industries (Care & cure providers, Medical suppliers/manufacturing, MedTech and Pharma & Life sciences). My responsibilities are to lead sell-side and buy-side due diligence engagements for a range of high-profile corporate and private equity clients. In these processes, we often work closely together with Deals Strategy (including Strategy&), Corporate Finance, Valuations and Operations colleagues. In addition, I have extensive experience in Business Restructuring Services, performing multiple Corporate review engagements during the COVID-19 pandemic.\n\nI have led due diligence processes for numerous Transactions in the past 12 years, ranging from large cross-border deals to small- and medium-sized domestic deals in various industries such as Retail & Consumer, Information Technology, Financial Services, Agriculture, Industrial Manufacturing & Automotive and in the past years mostly within Health Industries. \n\nEducation-wise I hold a MSc in Business Administration and completed the Executive Master of Finance and Control (RC) in 2015 at the VU University in Amsterdam (cum laude).",
